Mining operations can vary greatly depending on the type of mineral being extracted, such as coal, iron, gold, copper, and diamonds.
Mines are often located in remote or rural areas where mineral deposits are abundant.
The process of mining involves drilling, blasting, digging, and hauling to extract ores from underground or open-pit mines.</p>

